CHIKUNGUNYA (03): INDONESIA, INDIA
*********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>


In this update:
[1] Indonesia - Sumatra
[2] Indonesia - Central Java (Brebes)
[3] Indonesia - Central Java (Pekalongan)
[4] India - West Bengal

******
[1] Indonesia - Sumatra
Date: Fri 7 Dec 2007
Source: Padang Ekspres [edited]


The illness chikungunya has become an epidemic in Padang City. The
illness was found in 77 cases in 3 outbreak areas. As prevention
efforts, the Health Service did fogging (fumigation) and provided
medical treatment to the sufferers.

The cases were found in the Jati Koto Tinggi District, Padang East
Subdistrict (34 cases), in the Rawang District (6 cases), and 37
cases in the Ranah District, Padang South Subdistrict.

This illness was caused by chikungunya virus spread by _Aedes
aegypti_ mosquito bites. Prevention efforts were carried out with
insecticide fogging in the 3 outbreak regions.

"Fogging is not the solution to resolve the problem of this illness.
This is because of the characteristics of fogging. Only prevention
efforts [are effective long-term], so [fogging] must be followed by
increasing the cleanliness of the residence environment to interrupt
the breeding cycle of these mosquitoes," said Efrida Aziz, the Health
Service head of Padang City.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

[This is the 1st report that ProMED has received of epidemic
chikungunya in Indonesia outside of Java.

An interactive map of Sumatra showing the location of Panange can be
accessed at:
<http://www.travelpost.com/AS/Indonesia/Sumatera_Barat/Padang/map/6705512>.
